{"ts":"2026-06-26T19:07:53.029Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Celebrating the Victory**\n\nI'm thrilled! The linter passed without a hitch. Now, I'm performing a self-review of the ROI page design, rigorously comparing it against my checklist. The goal is premium quality, ensuring every element, from interactive inputs to visual clarity, screams custom elegance, and I am on track to meet that goal.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Visual Narrative**\n\nI've been examining the page's narrative flow. It centers around \"The Sovereignty Dividend,\" dynamically adjusting based on user selections and inputs. I'm focusing on the visual hierarchy – three telemetry cards lead into an editorial summary, then the SVG waterfall, and finally, scenario cards. I'm excited about the custom SVG waterfall chart mapping overhead to dividends, with its glowing gradient bars and connectors.\n\n\n**Assessing the Mobile Experience**\n\nI've just confirmed the mobile layout is top-notch, leveraging a responsive Tailwind grid for optimal display across devices. Interactions are genuinely useful, driving real-time updates across the analysis. The design is in line with the approved landing page theme, and I am avoiding AI-generated placeholders, ensuring every element has a strategic purpose. No unnecessary pills were added.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T19:07:53.032Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"3mpx3ylk","input":{"summary":"Built a premium, custom, and highly interactive ROI Results & Scenario Comparison console at `/app/build/roi/page.tsx`.\n\n### Design and Narrative Plan:\n1. **Strategic Narrative**: Configured as \"The Sovereignty Dividend.\" Models the fiscal benefit and reclaimed workforce hours resulting from migrating legacy processes to GFF AI secure multi-agent systems.\n2. **Visual Metaphor**: Designed as a premium, low-latency financial/operational dashboard with detailed security telemetry.\n3. **Waterfall Visual Idea**: Built a live, responsive SVG-based Waterfall Chart that dynamically recalculates and animates based on active input parameters to illustrate the path from Operational Friction to Net Sovereign Dividend.\n4. **Comparative Scenario Matrix**: Added three-way comparative cards representing Conservative (50% Adoption), Expected (85% Adoption - GFF Target), and Aggressive (120% Productivity Acceleration) pathways.\n5. **Interactive Live Controls**: Provided high-precision sliders synchronized with numeric input fields for:\n   - Workforce Size (FTEs)\n   - Avg Hourly Labor Rate ($/hr)\n   - Wasted Hours per FTE per week\n   - Initial CapEx Enclave Allocation ($)\n   - Strategic Priority objective grid\n6. **Actions & CTAs**: Added copy-to-clipboard for a beautifully formatted executive Markdown summary, a reset trigger, and three strategic next-step pipeline cards linking directly to the Diagnostic Assessor, Blueprint Architect, and SOW Proposal Studio.\n\n### Validation Done:\n- Passed strict static type checking with `npx tsc --noEmit` (0 errors, 100% compliant).\n- Passed standard ESLint rules with `npm run lint` (0 errors).\n- Confirmed zero impact on the approved landing page or other site files.","verified":true}}}
